List folders and files:
	ls <dir> <parameter>

	examples:
	ls -a (list all files, even hidden ones)
	ls -h (list in human format)

Change Directory:
	cd <dir>
	
	examples
	cd .. (go back)
	cd ~ (go to beginning)

Create New Dir(ectory):
	mkdir <name>

Delete Dir(ectory):
	rmdir <name>

Move file / Change Name:
	mv <path/name> <path/name>
	
	tip. you can use to change files name
	mv /home/user/test.txt /home/user/newname.txt
	
Create a txt:
	touch <name>
	
Delete file:
	rm <name>

Copy file:
        cp <path/name> <path/name>

Clear Terminal Screen:
	clear
	or
	Ctrl+L

Open New Terminal Session:
	Ctrl+Alt+T

End Session:
	exit
	or
	Ctrl+D

Copy something in Terminal:
	Ctrl+Shift+C

Paste in Terminal
	Ctrl+Shift+V

Show History
	history
	*history -c (clear history)
